  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n\r\n \r\n  \r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">THERMOMETER AND HEAT ENERGY<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Thermometers are instrument for measuring temperature. There are different types of thermometer;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Liquid in glass thermometer<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The thermometric substance in liquid in glass thermometer is Mercury or alcohol.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The physical property is change in volume of liquid with temperature.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Alcohol has advantage over mercury by having a low freezing point and higher expansivity. Mercury does not wet glass, it has higher conductivity and not easily vaporized.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Gas Thermometer<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Gas thermometer has gas as thermometric substance.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The physical property is change of gas pressure at constant volume with temperature.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Resistance Thermometer<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The thermometric substance is resistance wire.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The physical property is the change in electrical resistance of wire with temperature.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Thermocouple<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The thermometric substance is two dissimilar metals like copper and constantan.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The physical property is the change in electrical potential difference (or current) between two metal junctions at different temperatures.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The thermometric property of a thermocouple is the change in<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. equivalent resistance, B. electromotive force, C. colour, D. pressure.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A clinical thermometer is different from other mercury in glass thermometers owing to<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. its long stem. B. the constriction on its stem. C. its wide range of temperature. D. the grade of mercury used in it.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A clinical thermometer is different from other mercury in glass thermometers owing to<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. its long stem. B. the constriction on its stem. C. its wide range of temperature. D. the grade of mercury used in it.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The thermometer whose reading is indicated by a change in colour of its thermometric property is the<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. bi-metallic strip thermometer, B. thermocouple, C. platinum resistance thermometer, D. optical pyrometer.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-left:36pt; margin-bottom:10pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "THERMOMETER AND HEAT ENERGY"
}